    "source_section_latex": "\\[ r_{1}=(0,0,-d/2), \\qquad r_{2}=(0,0,d/2). \\] The field produced by a single dipole at position $r_{0}$ is \\[ B_{\\mathrm{dip}}(r;\\mu,r_{0}) = \\frac{\\mu_{0}}{4\\pi} \\left[ \\frac{3(r-r_{0})\\bigl(\\mu\\cdot(r-r_{0})\\bigr)}{\\lvert r-r_{0}\\rvert^{5}} - \\frac{\\mu}{\\lvert r-r_{0}\\rvert^{3}} \\right]. \\] The total internal field is \\[ B_{\\mathrm{total}}(r,t) = B_{\\mathrm{dip}}(r;\\mu_{1}(t),r_{1}) + B_{\\mathrm{dip}}(r;\\mu_{2}(t),r_{2}) + B_{\\mathrm{constraint}}(r,t). \\]\n\n\\[\n\\mathbf{r}_{+}=a\\hat{\\mathbf{z}},\\qquad \\mathbf{r}_{-}=-a\\hat{\\mathbf{z}}\n\\]\n\\[\n\\mathbf{B}_{\\mathrm{dip}}(\\mathbf{r};\\mathbf{m})=\\frac{\\mu_{0}}{4\\pi}\\frac{3\\hat{\\mathbf{r}}(\\mathbf{m}\\cdot\\hat{\\mathbf{r}})-\\mathbf{m}}{\\lVert\\mathbf{r}\\rVert^{3}}\n\\]"
